<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCAFFE8FF3D8571FE6AF9E9" box="[189,449,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Caucaseuma strasseri</emphasis>
Antić
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26C7A46FFCAFFE8FD8F8571FDC1F9EE" box="[527,618,1634,1660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B941B2FFFCAFFE8FF3D8596FD4EF90D" blockId="2.[189,816,1457,1695]" box="[189,741,1669,1695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCAFFE8FF3D8596FD4EF90D" authority="Antic &amp; Makarov, 2016" authorityName="Antic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2016" box="[189,741,1669,1695]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Caucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabile">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCAFFE8FF3D8596FE6DF90D" box="[189,454,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Caucaseuma variabile</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA66DEFFCAFFE8FE4D8596FD4EF90D" author="Antic D. Z. &amp; Makarov S. E." box="[461,741,1669,1695]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 205" refId="ref6352" refString="Antic D. Z. &amp; Makarov S. E. 2016. The Caucasus as a major hotspot of biodiversity: evidence from the millipede family Anthroleucosomatidae (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida). Zootaxa 4211 (1): 1 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4211.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Antić &amp; Makarov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33148A4FFCAFFE8FF3D85D5FADEF871" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B941B2FFFCAFFE8FF3D85D5FE9DF972" blockId="2.[189,310,1734,1760]" box="[189,310,1734,1760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
<heading id="D0DCAC43FFCAFFE8FF3D85D5FE9DF972" bold="true" box="[189,310,1734,1760]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCAFFE8FF3D85D5FE9DF972" bold="true" box="[189,310,1734,1760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B941B2FFFCAFFE8FF3D85E6FADEF871" blockId="2.[189,1399,1781,2019]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">
Differs from all other genera of the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCAFFE8FD3285E6FC14F89D" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1899" box="[690,959,1781,1807]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Anthroleucosomatidae</taxonomicName>
, except the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCAFFE8FB1585E5FE4AF8A0" authority="Antic &amp; Makarov, 2016" authorityName="Antic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2016" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Heterocaucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCAFFE8FB1585E5FADDF89D" box="[1173,1398,1782,1807]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Heterocaucaseuma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBA66DEFFCAFFE8FF3D840BFE4AF8A0" author="Antic D. Z. &amp; Makarov S. E." box="[189,481,1816,1842]" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" pagination="1 - 205" refId="ref6352" refString="Antic D. Z. &amp; Makarov S. E. 2016. The Caucasus as a major hotspot of biodiversity: evidence from the millipede family Anthroleucosomatidae (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida). Zootaxa 4211 (1): 1 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4211.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Antić &amp; Makarov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by the presence of two pairs of flagelliform processes originating from the base of the angiocoxites of the posterior gonopods. From the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCAFFE8FC54842FFB1EF8C7" authorityName="Antic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2016" box="[980,1205,1852,1877]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Heterocaucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCAFFE8FC54842FFB1EF8C7" box="[980,1205,1852,1877]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Heterocaucaseuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs by the presence of more complicated anterior gonopods, characterized by angiocoxites clearly differentiated into anterior and posterior parts. The anterior parts are shield-like, separated, partially fused or completely fused, with a visible furrow. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCAFFE8FD2684B5FC2CF82D" authorityName="Antic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2016" box="[678,903,1958,1983]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Heterocaucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCAFFE8FD2684B5FC2CF82D" box="[678,903,1958,1983]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="92">Heterocaucaseuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by somewhat simplified anterior gonopods with angiocoxites differentiated into a medial part, fully fused, and two lateral parts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33148A4FFCBFFE9FF3D821BFDB0FE0A" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B941B2FFFCBFFE9FF3D821BFEFDFEB0" blockId="3.[189,342,264,290]" box="[189,342,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">
<heading id="D0DCAC43FFCBFFE9FF3D821BFEFDFEB0" bold="true" box="[189,342,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCBFFE9FF3D821BFEFDFEB0" bold="true" box="[189,342,264,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B941B2FFFCBFFE9FF3D8224FDB0FE0A" blockId="3.[189,1398,311,408]" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCBFFE9FEC18224FE72FEC3" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1970" box="[321,473,311,337]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Caucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCBFFE9FEC18224FE72FEC3" box="[321,473,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">Caucaseuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes mainly narrow endemics confined to the Western and North Western Caucasus, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2B60ACFFCBFFE9FDBB8248FD63FEE6" authorityName="Antic &amp; Makarov" authorityYear="2016" box="[571,712,346,373]" class="Diplopoda" family="Anthroleucosomatidae" genus="Caucaseuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chordeumatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabile">
<emphasis id="B95FC73DFFCBFFE9FDBB8248FD63FEE6" box="[571,712,346,373]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">C. variabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a rather disjunct distribution in the western, northern and central Caucasus (
<figureCitation id="131007AAFFCBFFE9FE45826EFDA1FE0A" box="[453,522,381,408]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1981,2007]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1196,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-179@3.[189,1398,1196,1938]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Distribution of the genus Caucaseuma Strasser, 1970." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6564619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6564619/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="93">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
